et a new skill to put a point in, is there a good place to level a monk through the teens near a monk trainer? I would assume Oasis but I hate it there. I wanted to go to the warrens but its so far from Qeynos, is Luclin an option?<br><br>Fourth Question - how do I keep 1hb/2hb/h2h with &gt;15 weight = while keeping these items on my person at all times? I am amazed at how hard it is to keep weight under this amount while carrying 4 or more heavy weapons!  Do you just run to the bank every few minutes or what? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Thanks for reading!<br><br>Initiate Jaen - Monk of Qeynos<br>Venerable Adon - High Priest of Rodcet Nife &amp; Tunare<br> <p><center><img src="http://formula119.com/eqtaa/animated_valetrian.gif" height="180" alt="Retired Artifact Collector"></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udaleb123.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daleb123</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Disciple</span><br>  Posts: 317<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/30/02 6:40:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1917.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Answers</span><hr size=1> &quot;My first question is, am I screwing myself majorly by not working h2h at low levels? Should I start going bare-fisted and work on that before its too late?&quot;<br><br>You aren't &quot;screwing yourself majorly&quot;, but you should work on the skill. I recommend getting a Hand to Hand weapon, and practicing now.<br><br><br><br>&quot;Second question is practice points - I have been hoarding them a bit for dumping into Feign Death when I get it, but am wondering if I should start putting them in mend, as it seems like it is lagging WAY behind and at skill 23 now it works very rarely.&quot;<br><br>While Feign Death is a key skill, it's really easy to practice - and so really easy to max out without spending a lot of practice points. I recommend using some of your points in Mend now, investing your time into advancing FD, then spending a bunch of hoarded practice points in Instill Doubt/Intimidation - since that's the hardest to raise.<br><br><br><br>&quot;Third question - at these low levels I need to fight near a monk trainer because it seems every level I get a new skill to put a point in, is there a good place to level a monk through the teens near a monk trainer? I would assume Oasis but I hate it there. I wanted to go to the warrens but its so far from Qeynos, is Luclin an option?&quot;<br><br>You've got until Level 15 before you get any key new skills. Hunt wherever you want to in the meantime, then journey to a trainer at level 15; buy a port if you feel it is worth the time savings.<br><br><br>&quot;Fourth Question - how do I keep 1hb/2hb/h2h with &gt;15 weight = while keeping these items on my person at all times? I am amazed at how hard it is to keep weight under this amount while carrying 4 or more heavy weapons! Do you just run to the bank every few minutes or what?&quot;<br><br>At low levels, there isn't much of a penalty for exceeding your weight limit, but I wouldn't go too far over. Remember that you have the option of carrying a single 1hb and a single 2h blunt weapon; you can use your fist as the other Dual Wield weapon. If you can afford one, buy a weight reducing container to store the weapon you aren't using at the moment. Always consider weight when selecting new armor pieces.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showPrevMessage?topicID=1917.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35